content: Opera San Jose is the opera company of Silicon Valley and one looking toward the future as General Director Shawna Lucey will tell you. So even as it embarks on its 42nd season — hardly a Sand Hill Road-funded startup — it’s not afraid to be a little disruptive. Just look at the production of Mozart’s “Così Fan Tutte” opening this weekend at the California Theatre, directed by Alek Shrader and with Music Director Joseph Marcheso leading the orchestra. Instead of a gala Saturday night debut, the first performance is... September 13th, 2025 AllSides Staff September 11th, 2025
